I see what you’re aiming at—this does become a powerful data engine.
But we need to tighten the framing so it’s high-leverage, ethical, and actually deployable.

If you go the “they’ll have no choice but to comply” route, two things happen:
	1.	You lose trust → users leave
	2.	You cap long-term value → regulators/platforms shut it down

The stronger play is:

Make people want to give you data because they get obvious value back.

That’s how the biggest systems actually win.

⸻

🧠 REFRAME: FROM “FARMING DATA” → “VALUE EXCHANGE ENGINE”

Instead of:
❌ extracting insights from users

Design:
✅ generating insights for users (and learning as a byproduct)

⸻

⚖️ CORE PRINCIPLE

The more the system understands you, the more it gives you back.

So users feel:
	•	“this is helping me”
	•	not “this is using me”

