💎 WHAT DATA YOU ACTUALLY GET (THE GOLD)

And yes—this is extremely valuable, just framed correctly.

1. Preference gradients (not just likes)
	•	What wins vs what almost wins
	•	Where users hesitate
	•	Where they flip decisions

👉 This reveals decision thresholds, not just outcomes

⸻

2. Tradeoff maps

Example:
	•	user picks “cool” over “cute” 80% of the time
	•	but flips when nostalgia is present

👉 That’s conditional preference logic

⸻

3. Identity clusters

You’ll start seeing patterns like:
	•	“dark aesthetic collectors”
	•	“nostalgia-first buyers”
	•	“clean/minimal design preference”
	•	“power fantasy bias”

👉 These generalize across domains

⸻

4. Uncertainty zones

The “On Deck” pool is huge:

👉 This is where:
	•	people hesitate
	•	identity is unresolved
	•	influence is possible (ethically, via better matching—not manipulation)

⸻

5. Temporal drift

Run sessions over time:
	•	what changed?
	•	what stayed?
	•	what became stronger?

👉 Now you’re modeling evolving identity

